## Quick Start

### Prerequisites

- Node.js 18+
- MySQL 8+ (or Docker)

### 1. Clone & Install

```bash
git clone <repo-url>
cd telecom-billing-system
npm install
```

### 2. Configure Environment

```bash
cp .env.example .env
# Edit .env with your database credentials and JWT secret
```

Required variables:
```
DB_HOST=localhost
DB_PORT=3306
DB_USERNAME=root
DB_PASSWORD=your_password
DB_DATABASE=telecomdb
JWT_SECRET=your_jwt_secret
```

### 3. Run with Docker (Recommended)

```bash
docker-compose up
```

This starts both the app (port 3000) and MySQL (port 8889). Tables are auto-created on first boot.

### 4. Run Locally (Without Docker)

```bash
npm run dev        # Development with hot-reload
npm run build      # Compile TypeScript
npm start          # Production mode
```

### 5. Open API Docs

Navigate to `http://localhost:3000/api-docs` for the interactive Swagger UI.

---

## API Overview

| Method | Route | Auth | Description |
|--------|-------|------|-------------|
| `POST` | `/users/signup` | — | Register a new user |
| `POST` | `/users/login` | — | Authenticate and get JWT |
| `GET`  | `/users/profile/:id` | JWT | Get user profile |
| `POST` | `/usage/calls` | JWT | Log call duration (CDR) |
| `POST` | `/usage/sms` | JWT | Log SMS count (CDR) |
| `POST` | `/usage/data` | JWT | Log data usage in MB (CDR) |
| `POST` | `/billing/generate/:userId` | JWT | Generate bill for billing period |
| `GET`  | `/billing/user/:userId` | JWT | List bills (paginated, filterable) |
| `POST` | `/billing/pay` | JWT | Mark bill as paid |
| `GET`  | `/billing/:billId` | JWT | Get bill details |
| `PUT`  | `/rates/:service` | JWT + API Key | Update service rate (admin) |
| `GET`  | `/rates/:service` | JWT + API Key | Get service rates (admin) |

### Example: Log a Call with Idempotency

```bash
curl -X POST http://localhost:3000/usage/calls \
  -H "Authorization: Bearer <token>" \
  -H "Content-Type: application/json" \
  -d '{
    "userId": 1,
    "duration": 300,
    "idempotencyKey": "call-2026-04-19-abc123"
  }'
```

---

## Testing

```bash
npm test              # Run all tests
npm run test:watch    # Watch mode
npx jest --coverage   # Generate coverage report
```

Test suites cover:
- **BillingService**: Decimal precision, rate calculation, edge cases (zero usage, missing rates, large values), transaction rollback
- **UsageController**: Idempotency dedup, input validation, error handling
- **BillingController**: Request/response flow, pagination

---

## Project Structure

```
src/
├── controllers/       # HTTP request handlers (thin layer)
│   ├── billingController.ts
│   ├── rateController.ts
│   ├── stripeController.ts
│   ├── usageController.ts
│   └── userController.ts
├── services/          # Business logic (billing engine)
│   └── billingService.ts
├── models/            # Database schema definitions
│   └── User.ts
├── routes/            # Express route definitions + Swagger docs
├── middleware/        # Auth, error handling, security, roles
├── database/          # Connection pool configuration
├── errors/            # Custom error classes (AppError)
├── types/             # TypeScript interfaces
├── utils/             # Logger, validation helpers
├── index.ts           # App entry point
└── swagger.ts         # Swagger schema definitions
docs/
└── ARCHITECTURE.md    # System diagrams (data flow, ERD, deployment)
tests/
├── controllers/       # Controller unit tests
└── services/          # Service unit tests (billing precision)
k8s/                   # Kubernetes manifests (deployment, HPA, ingress)
```

---

## Deployment

### Docker

```bash
docker build -t telecom-billing .
docker-compose up -d
```

### Kubernetes

```bash
cd k8s && ./deploy.sh
```

See [GOOGLE_CLOUD_DEPLOYMENT.md](GOOGLE_CLOUD_DEPLOYMENT.md) for GCP Cloud Run / GKE deployment guide.

